description: D.E.A. Agent Summers and her partner, the mysterious Lunita are being hunted by the nebulous organization that traffics with the supernatural drug across Europe. They have to hide in the deep of the woods. Ancient forests, plenty of tales, legends, and mythical creatures that could be real!
name: One Cats Story

description: The visions of illustrator Lorenzo Sperlonga are enjoyed the world over, and this massive collection shows why. In this German 'Euro-Edition' of Dirty Works, a completely uncensored and eye-opening presentation is made, which includes his finest paintings and intricate step-by-step tutorials. Text is in both German and English, and the production and printing is spectacular. Oversized format.
name: Lorenzo Sperlonga: Dirty Works

description: El Gunto, aka Guillaume Poux, was born one day in April 1980. After many years in school to study as useless as mathematics or physical materials, he decided to learn a real serious business that will (almost) famous: cartoonist. Since then, he has published several comics and illustrated books from different publishers like Bamboo and Sun, while keeping some free time to draw pretty pin-ups, his besetting sin. French Text.
name: Vol. 1

description: Mike Hawthorne, an American artist, designer, and cartoonist, has been nominated for both an Eisner and Harvey awards, and he's worked with clients like FOX Films, Universal Studios, The 76ers, Marvel Comics, DC/Vertigo, Dark Horse Comics, IDW Publishing, and well as many others. He is currently working on his first French series, a three volume adaptation of Stefan Wul's science fiction classic Oms en Serie. French and English text.
name: Vol. 1

description: Sailing has always been at the discretion of a world imbued with the patina of time and boundless admiration for great artists such as Petty, Vargas, Gil Elvgren, Maly Siri has specialized over the years in the design of pin-up with a mind geared toward nostalgia. Through this sketchbook we find pleasure in the vamps rouged look, 'girls-next-door,' the characters of western outlined for Flipville (Ed. Dupuis) and sketches taken from the daily Montreal life of this young French illustrator. French text.
name: Vol. 1

description: Sketchbook Mara is a melting pot of everything she likes to draw, every styles she wants to experience. This book reveals the artistic personality of Margaux Kindhauser, aka Mara, who is fond of spontaneity and sketched drawings. In Mara's world, women are sometimes mermaids, sometimes Belle Epoque pinups wearing girdles, or Art Nouveau ladies inspired by Alfons Mucha; Escaped from the Victorian Era, from a fantasy world or even from a steampunk atmosphere.
name: Vol. 1

description: The sketchbook will include many sketches, new as the oldest, illustrations, research Ashrel, and many other discoveries! French text.
name: Vol. 1

description: Take a closer look into the web-filled world of one of the world's favorite super-heroes, Spider-Man! Featuring detailed profiles of over 200 of Spidey's friends and foes, as well as tons of facts and information on the Web-Slinger himself, the Spider-Man Character Encyclopedia will test your knowledge of the world of Spider-Man. Organized alphabetically, each character profile is crammed with facts, statistics, informative annotations, and exciting original comic book art illustrated by Marvel's leading artists.
name: HC

description: Throughout the universe there is one constant; everything dies. Growing up on the streets, losing everyone closest to him, Thaniel knows this harsh reality all too well. Born with a mysterious power that he's struggling to control, Thaniel begins to wonder if those he loves are gone because of him.

Ancient mythology and science fiction meet on ancient Earth! The war in ancient Egypt is here! It will take all of their skill and cunning for the hopelessly outnumbered Ulympeans to pull off a victory against the entrenched Tytans. If they lose, mankind will forever be under the thumb of Kronos and his minions. If they win, will mankind be any better off? The fate of the world hangs in the balance!
name: Vol. 3

description:
Young recruits Harry Blake and Charlie Yates had signed up for the infantry but ended up being sent to a tunnelling unit on the Western Front, part of a team of Royal Engineers - or "Sappers" as they were more commonly known.

Although the Sappers usually laboured beneath the trenches, rather than in them - their work was every bit as dangerous. And soon the pals realised that the fighting underground could be every bit as fierce as that on the surface...
name: The Fighting Sappers

description:
It was known to British and Germans alike in that bullet-raked valley as "The Villa In No-Man's-Land" - a bleak, deserted house commanding vital sections of each front line. But this was no ordinary house...

Nazi officers who took possession of it were found stiff and dead at their dinner-table. British patrols who moved up to investigate were never seen again. There were rumours of mysterious sounds heard underground, of secret passages and tunnels, of invisible voices and footsteps.

Then Sergeant Gunson and three Commandos were detailed to investigate - and execute - whoever or whatever was haunting the "Villa In No-Man's-Land".

Introduction

Chaco's cover and the title tell you the whole story, don't they? A Commando squad on an assassination mission ready to strike…except that this Powell story has an unexpected surprise which takes the whole plot in a different direction. It does something that is difficult to pull off in a Commando story; it has all its action compressed into a short time frame and takes place in a very small area. That could easily be a recipe for a long series of repetitive pictures but, thanks to the skill of the author and artist Bielsa, it's not.

Go on, read it and see if you agree.

Calum Laird, Commando Editor

Note: Originally released as Commando No 118 (May 1964) and was re-issued as No 647 (May 1972).
name: The Executioners

description:
By 1945, Sergeant Joe Kellis and his Sherman tank crew knew that the end of the war in Europe was in sight. They were hoping that it might end quietly for them.

Then their tank was hijacked by a couple of Italian deserters and they found themselves mixed up in a dangerous scheme involving stolen gold that could see them on the run from both sides.

A quiet end to the War...? Not a chance!
name: Hi-Jacked!

description:
The raiders' objective was vital. If they reached and destroyed their target, it would be a bitter blow to the enemy. But the greatest danger the forward recce party faced came from within their own ranks...the result of an old grudge which could only mean BIG trouble.

Introduction

What's in a name? Or rather, a title?

Here, author Peter McKenzie's working title was "A Question Of Trust". Personally, I think that's a great title - one which neatly sums up the underlying theme of this tough action-packed tale.

However, as good as it is, that title doesn't quite match up with artist Jeff Bevan's inventive, offbeat cover. The more robust, straight-forward "Sabotage Mission" fits the bill perfectly. Where possible we would always try to use a writer's original title but the Commando editorial team from 1989 made the right decision in changing it.

Scott Montgomery, Deputy Editor

Note: Originally released as Commando No 2321 (October 1989).
name: Sabotage Mission

description:
Living in the margins of the X-Men, Doop has freaked out X-Men and readers alike. However, when he gets deeply involved in X-Men business (and in the personal life of Kitty Pryde!), Doop will be thrust into the spotlight. This adventure will prove that Doop is, in fact, the most powerful X-Man! Written by co-creator Peter Milligan (X-FORCE), covers by co-creator Mike Allred (X-FORCE, FF) and innovative interior art by David Lafuente (AVENGERS, ULTIMATE SPIDER-MAN)!

description: The first issue of the OMNIPATHY series. This issue contains two 4-page, self-contained short stories as well as some additional art. Includes astronauts, lumberjacks, sheep and labyrinth-bound metaphysical space-minotaurs.

The second issue of the OMNIPATHY series. This issue contains a single 11-page, full-colour story. A young man in the Phillipines gets caught up in a coral-stealing racket and learns that sometimes thievery isn't worth the price.

The third issue of the OMNIPATHY series, and the largest yet. This issue contains two 11-page, full-colour stories: a race of bizarre aliens discover a mysterious artifact beyond their comprehension, and a court jester is given the insurmountable task of defeating a murderous dragon.

volume.name: The Psychedelic Journal of Time Travel

description: A journal containing fourteen black/white and full color short stories all involving time travel.

volume.name: The Psychedelic Journal of Time Travel
No Need for Tenchi! Part Eleven

description: Callum and Henry concoct a plan that could solve all their problems. What could possibly go wrong?

In the Rahal family tomb, Victoria Addair discovers a dark secret that could provide the answers she needs as to the identity of The Grey Boy. As Cold Ones rise and turn their attentions toward the Rahals, the Black Hand serves as the family's last line of defense.

Jerome begins to train his body to fight an ancient evil that may be responsible for his niece's disappearance. When Gwendolyn rejoins the Council of the God Children they begin to discuss their next move. Are they all on the same page or do some of them have other plans?
Shane chases his son through the labyrinthine battlefield of Max's memories and fears. Will he find a way out, and can he trust that path?

Birdie and her sister Abigail have a secret... a secret about dead rats... dead rats dancing. But the rats were just the beginning of the horror that unfolds around them. Cole Jensen has secrets of his own. And he'll go to awful lengths to keep them hidden.
name: Part 2 of 4

volume.name: Make Room for Monsters and Wildlife on the Land

description: The terrifying conclusion to the critically acclaimed series from comics legend Kurt Busiek! After a powerful, predatory corporation acquires Dracula as a valuable asset, they soon discover one terrifying truth: no one can own the Son of the Dragon! As the vampire armies of the corporation and Dracula face off against each other, Evan must enter into an unlikely alliance with Marta and her team of vampire hunters. Can Evan and Marta work together long enough to rally a rebellion that will be able to withstand the onslaught?
name: Volume Three

description: In this cinematic prelude to Amazing Spider-Man 2, we catch up with Peter Parker as he juggles his life as a super hero, his relationship with Gwen Stacy, and his new responsibilities as a freelance photographer. When he encounters a robbery-in-progress at a warehouse containing a mysterious piece of tech, Spider-Man swings into action like never before in a full-blown Infinite Comic extravaganza. Don't miss this all-new lead-in to the upcoming "The Amazing Spider-Man 2"!

Archer Coe is a professional hypnotist whose performances will "pierce the eggshell of your brain and stir up the yolk." This has lead him to unexpected places, and made him the focus of unforeseen attention. After one of his shows, he's confronted by a mysterious man who wants to know if Archer makes house calls. The answer to the question, and the strange conspiracy it will unlock, is only the beginning of Archer Coe's troubles.
name: Chapter 1

volume.name: Archer Coe and the Thousand Natural Shocks

description: What are the causes and consequences of climate change? When the scale is so big, can an individual make any difference? Documentary, diary, and masterwork graphic novel, this up-to-date look at our planet and how we live on it explains what global warming is all about. With the most complicated concepts made clear in a feat of investigative journalism by artist Philippe Squarzoni, Climate Changed weaves together scientific research, extensive interviews with experts, and a call for action. Weighing the potential of some solutions and the false promises of others, this groundbreaking work provides a realistic, balanced view of the magnitude of the crisis that An Inconvenient Truth only touched on.
name: GN

volume.name: Climate Changed: A Personal Journey Through the Science

name: Le Bleu est une Coleur Chaude

description: The Eisner Award-winning team behind 100 BULLETS reunites to tell the story of the baddest Minuteman of all. When last we saw Lono in 100 BULLETS, Dizzy Cordova had shot him in the chest ... but Lono always was too tough to die. Now, Lono finds himself in Mexico working on the side of the angels. Collects the entire eight-issue miniseries.
name: TPB

"Beautiful Beasts!" Collects Nightmares and Fairy Tales (2002) #7-12. By Serena Valentino. Haunting stories from fairy tales to a '40s murder-mystery thriller fill this collection of the gorgeous fan-favorite horror series about ghostly love, the souls of dead children and beasts who are beauties and beauties who are beasts.
name: Beautiful Beasts

description: Albert the Alien, the first exchange student from the stars, must save the school from his over-fed (and still hungry) alien lunch! It has decided that humans are delicious, and has started eating everything in sight! Can Albert stop this alien slime ball and save the school from

Petula is a beautiful cow who smells nice, has pretty hair, and makes Ariol tremble when she's around. And even though Ariol's story so far is almost 400 pages long, he still hasn't worked up the courage to tell Petula that he loves her! Instead, he keeps accidentally saying all the wrong things every time she turns around to talk to him in class. Valiant Ariol is finally ready to make his move. Will he soar like Thunder Horse or plummet like, well, like Ariol?

With charming artwork and hilarious vignettes, Ariol is the perfect series for anyone who started off life as a kid!

Note: The digital edition (4/9/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: A Beautiful Cow

description: Shifting between realities, Simon and Ethan track Ash back to the Black Hole Cafe, but is it too late?

Gavin and Doug are two juvenile delinquents drinking in a cemetery one night who get caught by Old Percy, the night watchman. Percy says they'll let him go if they listen to his story about how when he was four years old he and hundreds of other children went looking for a vampire there...and found him!

The path of Virtue takes unexpected turns, and the troubles of Jeff and his alter-egos ensnare unintended victims. Jeff seeks help yet again from the dubious Doctor Atomic, and an electrifying secret is revealed!

Falling Down, Fading Through

Colby explores a mysterious portal with devastating results for both himself and Iris.
name: Chapter 12: The Stealing Spark

volume.name: Makeshift Miracle: The Girl From Nowhere

description: As Eric wakes up on the morning after his kidnapping, Lola, a young reporter for a tabloid, gets a hold of a set of surprising photos.
name: Vol. 5

description:
Demonman and Telex are on a double date. Everything was going well until a ninja appeared out of nowhere and tried to steal Demonman's date's purse.

Issue #2 ended with Demonman, Telex and their dates surrounded by ninjas.

Misfits #3 sees the Misfits square off against The Ninja Master, the lamest villain in recent history. The only problem is that the Misfits must first deal with Ninja Master's horde of hundreds of ninjas.

This issue is action-packed and extremely violent. Not for the faint-of-heart.
name: The Ninja Master

description:
Following the shocking events from the previous issue, Alanis finds herself trapped within the Abyss while her physical body deteriorates in the real world. Learn the secrets of her past and discover the history of the NEVERMINDS organization as this turning point issue will leave you guessing what comes next!

NEVERMINDS is the code name for a secret, superhuman organization that offers security and investigation...for a fee. Created as a training ground for those with unique abilities, it slowly developed into a team of individuals that longed to serve a greater purpose.

HelloMyNameIs

When a young man is murdered, his father, a professional hitman, will go on a killing spree to have his vengeance; even if the killer is the son of one of the most powerful people in the city. The chief of Police.
name: HelloMyNameIs

description: "The Matador" closes the gap on his search as our hero finds a new lead on finding his home. Decisions must be made that may cost the lives of those close to him.

The world's greatest superhero cat fetches five new solo tales featuring his nine lives! The witch's cat puts a hex on black magic! The cyborg cat saves the city! The theater cat overcomes the uncouth! The Shaolin cat fights a bear! And Scratch himself reaches new levels of adventure! Fun for all-ages!

The brand new world of Sonic the Hedgehog barrels ahead at breakneck speed with "The Chase" Part Two: Sonic fights for his life against a NEW terrifying super-badnik! Just to make matters worse, they're battling on an out-of-control train! With Dr. Eggman waiting at the depot, Sonic's in a fight against time -- and killer robots! Featuring high-speed cover art from Sonic artist supreme TRACY YARDLEY!

Note: The digital edition (4/9/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: The Chase: Part Two

description: The classic sci-fi film from Legend Films gets updated in this new modern comic version. Will Gary survive the attack of the giant spider? Will the queen find out the true identity of her lost love? Is the moon really made of cheese? Find out all the answers to these questions. Extras include stills and never before seen images from the cult classic by Legend Films.

Blast off for adventure with the world's first/worst Astrochimp, Bops, as he finds himself transported to the distant planet Centroa. With the aid of his diminutive cohort Max and an outcast Scrounger named Sh'A La, Bops struggles to recover his missing spaceship and return home, even as the agents of the evil Overlord Jardu Krush close in around him. All-ages action-comedy. This issue has never before seen images and character designs!

Join us for the final chapter of this blood soaked trilogy of murder, mayhem and mammaries. Theodore Paulsen comes face to face with true terror in a final showdown which will shock and discombobulate you. See the final events unfold in dramatic and cinematic fashion akin to a classic Hammer Horror movie. This shocking conclusion will resonate with you long after you're done reading it and will have you starting the series from the beginning again and again.

Thick as Thieves

King Raimundo braces the Sapphire Kingdom as an unknown army descends upon them, and where the hell is Lord Orfio?

Next, Tristan discovers the identity of the mysterious thief girl who attacked him. How is she tied to his past?

Finally in Chapter 3 "A Thief Came to Dance", enter Lord Vasuman!

The adventure continues in Thief of Hearts issue 2

Rue, Jack and Jade search for Quinn's treasure, but are beset by a gang of tasmanian devils, and nearly lose everything in a fiery conflagration.

description:
Space Corps 0 collects four short stories penned by indie comic creators Bryan Richmond, Gannon Beck, and Joey Groah. Each story focuses on a different member of the Space Corps--a band of marines from various worlds committed to protecting sentient life from galactic annihilation.

The three stories are:

  • "Rockeater"
  • "Outnumbered"
  • "Lizard's Tale"
  • "Living Breath"
